definition.value: A grape berry food product which results from crushing whole (destemmed) grapes and which contains grape juice and components of grape pomace.
A grape pressing process in which whole grapes or destemmed grape must is input directly into a grape press.
A grape pressing process in which whole grapes and grape clusters are input directly into a grape press.
By avoiding a maceration process, this technique limits the extraction of phenolics into white wines.
A food component separation process that accomplishes grape crushing and destemming with one device.
This process may be carried out by a "stemmer-crusher" aka "destemmer-crusher".

Grape juice which has been extracted through the process of crushing, the natural break down of the grape cell walls during maceration or fermentation, and/or by the weight of grapes within a tall container.
Grape juice which is extracted from grapes using a grape pressing process.

Pressed juice often has lower acidity levels, higher potassium and pH level, more phenolic compounds such as tannins and more suspended solids such as natural gum and proteins. [wikipedia:Pressing_(wine)#Free-run_versus_pressed_juice]
